Depends: python3 (>= 3.10), python3-click (>= 8.1.0), python3-rich (>= 13.0.0)
Recommends: apt, snapd, flatpak, pacstall, appimage
Maintainer: undefinederror <github@object.ninja>
Description: Ubuntu Package Kit - Universal package manager wrapper
 UPK is a unified CLI for managing packages across multiple package managers
 on Ubuntu systems. It provides a single interface to search, install, update,
 and remove packages from APT, Snap, Flatpak, Pacstall, and AppImage sources.
 .
 Features:
  - Search packages across all configured backends
  - Install packages with interactive source selection
  - Install local files (.deb, .AppImage)
  - Install remote files from URLs
  - Update package lists and upgrade packages
  - Remove packages with automatic source detection
  - List installed packages with filtering
  - Configuration system for customizing behavior
